    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix segmentation fault in NGAP handover cancel encoding function\n\n### Summary\nThe newly implemented `encode_ng_handover_cancel` function in the NGAP context management procedures was causing a segmentation fault when called with valid parameters. This was due to incorrect structure naming in the ASN.1 encoding logic.\n\nThe issue occurred when attempting to encode HandoverCancel messages, causing the gNB to crash during handover procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_context_management_procedures.c`: Corrected structure type names from `NGAP_HandoverCancelIEs_t` to `NGAP_HandoverCancel_IEs_t` to match ASN.1 generated naming conventions\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_context_management_procedures.c`: Fixed corresponding value union member names from `NGAP_HandoverCancelIEs__value_PR_*` to `NGAP_HandoverCancel_IEs__value_PR_*`\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a handover scenario between gNBs\n2. Trigger a handover cancel event\n3. Call `encode_ng_handover_cancel` with valid UE context and cause parameters\n4. Observe segmentation fault due to undefined structure references\n\nThe crash occurs in the ASN.1 encoding layer when trying to access non-existent structure members.\n"
}